config RGB_INDICATOR
    bool "Custom per-key RGB layer indicator"
    depends on LED_STRIP
    default n
    help
      Drives the per-key SK6812 chain directly (via the Zephyr led_strip API)
      for layer-based indication. Mutually exclusive in practice with ZMK's
      own RGB underglow driver, which should be disabled so there is only one
      writer to the strip.

config RGB_INDICATOR_MAP_MODE
    bool "LED chain mapping mode (walking dot)"
    depends on RGB_INDICATOR
    default n
    help
      Temporary diagnostic: light one LED at a time (index 0 = blue anchor,
      others red), advancing ~1.5s, looping. Used once to discover the
      physical chain index -> key mapping. Turn off for normal operation.
